aces the methods and imaginaries through which family planning calculated lives not worth living, lives not worth saving, and lives not worth being born. The resulting archive of thick data transmuted into financialized "Invest in a Girl" campaigns that reframed survival as a question of human capital. The book challenges readers to reject the economy as our collective container and to refuse population as a term of reproductive justice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aBangladesch. 0aBevölkerungsentwicklung. 0aFamilienplanung. 0aFamily planningxEconomic aspects. 0aFamily policyxEconomic aspects. 0aFertility, HumanxPolitical aspects. 0aFertility, HumanxSocial aspects. 0aFertilität. 0aUSA. 0aWert des Menschenlebens. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2017z978311069634940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822373216zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822373216423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822373216.jpg  a978-3-11-069634-9  DUK eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles